=== Patched evidence: UE-357736-fix.patch validation on Unreal Engine 5.7.4 source ===

Source: PIE Output Log from M_Repro.umap with the patch applied to a source-build
clone of UE 5.7.4 at the 5.7.4-release tag. Patched binary built locally via
Engine/Build/BatchFiles/Build.bat UnrealEditor Win64 Development. Verified the
incremental rebuild touched NetActorFactory.cpp (Module.Engine.44.cpp recompiled,
UnrealEditor-Engine.dll relinked).

Filter (identical to baseline-evidence.log):
- LogCsvProfiler: iris="..."                  (confirms Iris is enabled)
- LogIris: ReplicationSystem ... is created   (confirms Iris init)
- LogNet: ... using replication model ...     (confirms NetDriver chose Iris)
- LogTemp: Warning: [Actor] BeginPlay -- Role=N

Project, PIE config, expected behaviour: identical to baseline (see baseline-evidence.log).

Result: every run shows 40/40 distinct Role=1 instance names on the client side
(vs the 32/40 seen in baseline). Zero silent subsets. The 8 actors that were
silent in the baseline are now visible via a SECOND WAVE of BeginPlay lines
arriving after the main NotifyBeginPlay wave -- which is exactly the patch's
new else-if-not-HasActorBegunPlay branch in UNetActorFactory::PostInit firing
during Loop 2 of FlushPostDispatchForBatch, after Loop 1's OnRep_ReplicatedHasBegunPlay
already ran. The recovered actors tick from the same frame onwards (same Tick
counter values), confirming no observable client-side delay.


